Prospective Ageing - Talk

This is the repo for an informal seminar I gave at the Oxford Institute of Population Ageing 21.11.2018.

It includes my first attempts at using gganimate to animate the charts and xarinang to make the slides.

Prospective Ageing

The talk is a descriptive one on what Prospective Age is, following Sanderson and Scherbov and what they call the Characteristics Approach to Population Ageing: New Measures. I then used the 10 countries represented in my audience to demonstrate the difference between restrospective and prospective measures of ageing.

Data

The data used here is sourced directly from the Prospective Age Dataset figshare deposit, which I prepared in this github repository. The underlying data is the 2017 Revision of the UN World Population Prospects.
